<paragraph blockId="11.[313,1269,625,1733]" pageId="11" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis box="[353,461,626,649]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="347">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="George" authorityYear="2004" box="[481,642,625,649]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haploniscidae" genus="Chandraniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[481,642,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="347">Chandraniscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with body broad and ovate. Cephalon with frontal margin concave and lacking any median projection. Lateral sutures between the anterior pereonites more pronounced from pereonites 1–5. Pleotelson with apex truncated and posterolateral projection not extending beyond the apex. Antenna 1 with peduncle of two articles, second article long, and a flagellum of four articles. Flagellum of antenna 2 composed of nine articles. Uropod uniramous, tip reaching to the tip of the posterolateral angle of pleotelson.
</paragraph>
